  <static seed="173" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring435.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{\left(a+b\right)x^{2}+19\mathopen{}\left(a+b\right)x+90\mathopen{}\left(a+b\right)}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\left(a+b\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+10\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+9\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>Let<rsq/>s start by noting that <m>(a+b)</m> is common to each term, so 
we may write</p>
<p><m>{\left(a+b\right)x^{2}+19\mathopen{}\left(a+b\right)x+90\mathopen{}\left(a+b\right)} = {\left(a+b\right)\mathopen{}\left(x^{2}+19x+90\right)}</m></p>
<p>Next we look for factors of <m>90</m> that give <m>19</m> when added; the 
factors that work are <m>10</m> and <m>9</m> so</p>
<p><m>{\left(a+b\right)x^{2}+19\mathopen{}\left(a+b\right)x+90\mathopen{}\left(a+b\right)}={\left(a+b\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+10\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+9\right)}</m></p>
<p>Note that this answer can be checked by using the FOIL (<alert>F</alert>irst <alert>O</alert>utside <alert>I</alert>nside <alert>L</alert>ast) technique (exercise).</p>
</solution>
